{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbfd63310-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s14925"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"14925"},"text":"§ 14925.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Universal accreditation requirements","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbfd63311-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s14925/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The provisions of title II and section 404 of the Intercountry Adoption Act of 2000 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s14901"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 14901","children":[],"tail":" et seq.[, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s14944"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 14944","children":[],"tail":"]), and related implementing regulations, shall apply to any person offering or providing adoption services in connection with a child described in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t8/s1101/b/1/F"},"text":"section 1101(b)(1)(F) of title 8","children":[],"tail":", to the same extent as they apply to the offering or provision of adoption services in connection with a Convention adoption. The Secretary of State, the Secretary of Homeland Security, the Attorney General (with respect to section 404(b) of the Intercountry Adoption Act of 2000 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s14944"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 14944","children":[],"tail":"[(b)])), and the accrediting entities shall have the duties, responsibilities, and authorities under title II and title IV of the Intercountry Adoption Act of 2000 ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s14921"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 14921","children":[],"tail":" et seq., 14941 et seq.] and related implementing regulations with respect to a person offering or providing such adoption services, irrespective of whether such services are offered or provided in connection with a Convention adoption."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbfd63312-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s14925/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Effective date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The provisions of this section shall take effect 18 months after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2013-01-14"},"text":"January 14, 2013","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbfd63313-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s14925/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Transition rule","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"This Act shall not apply to a person offering or providing adoption services as described in subsection (a) in the case of a prospective adoption in which—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfd63314-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s14925/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" an application for advance processing of an orphan petition or petition to classify an orphan as an immediate relative for a child is filed before the date that is 180 days after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2013-01-14"},"text":"January 14, 2013","children":[],"tail":"; or"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfd63315-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s14925/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the prospective adoptive parents of a child have initiated the adoption process with the filing of an appropriate application in a foreign country sufficient such that the Secretary of State is satisfied before the date that is 180 days after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2013-01-14"},"text":"January 14, 2013","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbfd63316-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/276/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–276, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2013-01-14"},"text":"Jan. 14, 2013","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/126/2466"},"text":"126 Stat. 2466","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbfd63317-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbfd63318-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idbfd63319-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Intercountry Adoption Act of 2000, referred to in subsec. (a), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/279"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–279","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-10-06"},"text":"Oct. 6, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/825"},"text":"114 Stat. 825","children":[],"tail":". Title II of the Act is classified principally to this subchapter, and title IV of the Act is classified generally to subchapter IV (§ 14941 et seq.) of this chapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s14901"},"text":"section 14901 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This Act, referred to in subsec. (c), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/276"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–276","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2013-01-14"},"text":"Jan. 14, 2013","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/126/2466"},"text":"126 Stat. 2466","children":[],"tail":", known as the Intercountry Adoption Universal Accreditation Act of 2012. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title of 2013 Amendment note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s14901"},"text":"section 14901 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idbfd6331a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the Intercountry Adoption Universal Accreditation Act of 2012, and not as part of the Intercountry Adoption Act of 2000 which comprises this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idbfd6331b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"definitions","id":"idbfd6331c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Definitions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/276/s4"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–276, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2013-01-14"},"text":"Jan. 14, 2013","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/126/2467"},"text":"126 Stat. 2467","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/112/276/s4"},"text":"“In this Act [see Short Title of 2013 Amendment note set out under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s14901"},"text":"section 14901 of this title","children":[],"tail":"], the terms ‘accrediting entity’, ‘adoption service’, ‘Convention adoption’, and ‘person’ have the meanings given those terms in section 3 of the Intercountry Adoption Act of 2000 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s14902"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 14902","children":[],"tail":").”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
